				<section id="about">
					<h1>About the <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr></h1>
					<p>
						The <strong>International Society for Phylogenetic Nomenclature</strong> was established to encourage and facilitate the development and use of, and communication about, phylogenetic nomenclature.
						Toward this end, the <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr> organizes periodic <strong>scientific meetings</strong> and oversees the implementation of a <strong>code of rules</strong> to govern phylogenetic nomenclature&mdash;the <strong><a href="/code"><cite><abbr title="International Code of Phylogenetic Nomenclature">PhyloCode</abbr></cite></a></strong>.
						<cite>PhyloCode</cite> names can be viewed and submitted via the registration database, <strong><a href="//phyloregnum.org">RegNum</a></strong>.
					</p>
					<p>
						The <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr> is governed by a <strong><a href="#council">Council</a></strong>, of which all members except the Program Director are elected.
						For more information, see the <a href="/pdf/ispn_bylaws.pdf">Bylaws (<abbr class="initialism">PDF</abbr>)</a>.
					</p>
					<p>
						The <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr> maintains two <strong>committees</strong> whose responsibilities pertain directly to the functioning of the <i>PhyloCode</i>: the <a href="#cpn">Committee on Phylogenetic Nomenclature</a> (<abbr class="initialism">CPN</abbr>) and the <a href="#reg">Registration Committee</a>.
						The members of both committees are elected by the <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr> membership.
					</p>
					<p>
						The <abbr class="initialism">CPN</abbr> is responsible for reviewing and approving changes to the <cite>PhyloCode</cite>.
						The <abbr class="initialism">CPN</abbr> also rules on proposals for conservation or suppression of names, resolves ambiguities in the provisions of the code, amends the provisions of the code, and will produce future editions of it.
					</p>
					<p>
						The Registration Committee is responsible for managing the online registration database for names governed by the <cite>PhyloCode</cite>.
					</p>
					<p>
						Anyone who is interested in phylogenetic nomenclature is encouraged to <strong><a href="/membership">join</a></strong> the <abbr class="initialism">ISPN</abbr>.
					</p>
